Drought may damage crops in Armenia - Berberyan

21.07.2015, 14:49
Dry weather in Armenia may damage potato, wheat and cabbage crops, Hrachya Berberyan, the head of Armenia's Farmers' Union, told journalists on Tuesday.  
YEREVAN, July 21. /ARKA/. Dry weather in Armenia may damage potato, wheat and cabbage crops, Hrachya Berberyan, the head of Armenia's Farmers' Union, told journalists on Tuesday.
